Q-what is multiThreading in java, and why it is important?
Multithreading is the execution of multiple threads in a process for faster performance.
eg: suppose a customer is placing an order:
sending email--- 1 thread
sending sms --- 2 thread
updating the inventory - 3 thread
making the payment - 4th thread
getting the order recieved successfully - 5th thread

These are the mutiple threads are working to achive a task for customer to place the order.

