Q-What are daemon Threads?
Daemon threads are the background threads which support the user threads.
A daemon thread is a low-priority background thread that automatically terminates when all user threads finish execution.
Eg: garbage collector, cache cleanup, Session cleanup.

Q-What is RaceCondition?
Race Condition is a scenario when a multiple threads try to access the same shared resource, resulting in incosistency behaviour.
It can be prevented using syncronization , atomic classes and locks.

